        options: ["Proceed with cardioversion immediately since the patient is hemodynamically stable","Perform transesophageal echocardiogram to exclude left atrial thrombus before cardioversion","Cancel cardioversion permanently as the patient is not a candidate","Administer aspirin instead of anticoagulation and proceed with cardioversion"],
        correct: 1,
        rationale: "If adequate anticoagulation for at least 3 weeks cannot be confirmed, a TEE must be performed to exclude left atrial appendage thrombus before elective cardioversion. Cardioverting a patient with an existing atrial thrombus can dislodge the clot and cause a stroke. Aspirin is not adequate stroke prophylaxis for cardioversion."
