        correct: 2,
        rationale: "Amiodarone is the ONLY antiarrhythmic considered safe in HFrEF. Flecainide and propafenone (Class IC) are contraindicated in structural heart disease (CAST trial). Dronedarone is specifically CONTRAINDICATED in heart failure -- the ANDROMEDA trial showed increased mortality in HF patients."
